  "event_preview": "Oxford Plains Speedway is a 0.375-mile (0.604 km) paved oval in Oxford, Maine, opened in 1950 and operating in its current configuration since a 1992 repaving and backstretch widening that expanded the layout from its original third-mile dimensions. The track seats 14,000 — the largest capacity of any sporting venue in Maine. Originally scheduled for May 2, the All States Materials Group 150 was postponed to Saturday, June 6, after a poor weather forecast and became the first Whelen Modified Tour visit to Oxford in 35 years. The series had previously raced here five times from the mid-1980s through the early 1990s, the last occasion being June 1991 when future Tour champion Jeff Fuller won. Previous Whelen Modified Tour winners at the Route 26 oval include NASCAR Hall of Famer Richie Evans, former Cup Series winner Jimmy Spencer, and longtime Xfinity Series standout Mike McLaughlin. The 150-lap race (56.25 miles) was contested as Race 4 of the 2026 season.\n\nJon McKennedy swept both practice sessions and dominated after passing polesitter Stephen Kopcik for the lead, scoring his second victory of 2026 and the first Modified Tour win at Oxford since 1991. Tyler Rypkema finished second in the No. 3 Ole Blue Modified — the only car in the field that also competed in the 1991 race here. The field raced without four-time champion and 48-time series winner Justin Bonsignore, who had withdrawn to reinvest in his program and also skipped the following Seekonk event — the first Modified Tour start he missed since October 2009.",
